Y \u2018Juniper\u2019 redesign might come soon", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-07-08T16:00:00+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A photo of a sign at the 2023 edition of Tokyo Game Show.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/tFvgrZH0XnyC4XJwlMO5klbIBgU=/0x0:4242x2828/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73449139/1681640286.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Tokyo Game Show</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n\n  \t\t <p>Workers in the country enjoy greater protection thanks to employment laws, but that doesn\u2019t mean Japan is anything close to a proletariat utopia. </p>\n  <p>\n    <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/24191650/nintendo-sega-from-software-japan-video-game-layoffs\">Continue reading&hellip;</a>\n  </p>", "id": 828738, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/24191650/nintendo-sega-from-software-japan-video-game-layoffs", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "How Japan has avoided the gaming industry\u2019s persistent layoffs", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-07-08T14:54:26+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Several rally cars racing on a track, with the lede car mid-drift.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/Fw8aVnwoZSCxA2VmTI8rdv_S_EY=/150x3:1214x712/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73448922/World_RX_Sweden.0.jpeg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: FIA World Rallycross Championship</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"xm8omy\">After two seasons of all-electric racing, the World Rallycross Championship (or World RX) held its first mixed powertrain races between electric and internal combustion engine (ICE) cars this weekend in H\u00f6ljes, Sweden. Unlike traditional point-to-point rally racing, rallycross puts those cars on a circuit, but with similar racing over dirt and gravel surfaces, as well as plenty of jumping and drifting through turns.</p>\n<p id=\"qXin2Y\">There were six EVs and four ICE cars in this weekend\u2019s races, and by the end of the first weekend, EV racers took up <a href=\"https://www.fiaworldrallycross.com/a/news/w28193_Rainmaster--Krist", "id": 828281, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/7/8/24193814/world-rx-ev-vs-ice-rallycross-racing", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "EVs are taking on combustion engines in a rallycross \u2018Battle of Technologies\u2019", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-07-08T14:00:00+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A photo illustration and portrait of Canva CEO and co-founder Melanie Perkins. \" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/MOtd1AT4eafyNbuAJXqyup_8VEA=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73448811/DCD_Melanie_Perkins.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Photo illustration by The Verge / Photo: Canva</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n\n  \t\t <p>To her, AI is just an extension of what Canva has always done: make accessible design tools that cost less than Adobe\u2019s. </p>\n  <p>\n    <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/24191080/canva-ceo-melanie-perkins-design-ai-adobe-competition-decoder-podcast-interview\">Continue reading&hellip;</a>\n  </p>", "id": 827846, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/24191080/canva-ceo-melanie-perkins-design-ai-adobe-competition-decoder-podcast-interview", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Canva CEO Melanie Perkins thinks the design world needs more alternatives to Adobe", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-07-08T13:41:47+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A photo showing CMF\u2019s Buds Pro 2 in their charging case\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/I5ODeSxA5XGR0zC7MGuMBhqmz30=/0x46:988x705/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73448774/cmf_budspro_2_3.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: CMF</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"bWw0O3\">Nothing\u2019s affordability-focused subbrand, CMF, launched more than just a <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/7/8/24191666/nothing-cmf-phone-1-cases-accessories-lanyard-wallet\">$199 smartphone today</a>. It also debuted a new pair of $59 wireless earbuds and a $69 smartwatch that incorporate the unique flair that Nothing has become known for.</p>\n<p id=\"Ir0llB\"><a href=\"https://cmf.tech/en-us/pages/buds-pro-2\">The Buds Pro 2</a> are CMF\u2019s follow-up <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2023/9/26/23891328/nothing-cmf-buds-pro-watch-charger\">to the earbuds it released</a> last year. Unlike CMF\u2019s first iteration of the Buds Pro (which are $10 cheaper), the Buds Pro 2 have", "id": 827512, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/7/8/24194066/nothing-cmf-buds-pro-2-watch-pro-2-launch", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Nothing\u2019s CMF launches new supercheap earbuds and a smartwatch", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-07-08T12:24:01+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Illustration of a person remote working from on top of their couch that is strapped to a car broken down in the desert.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/c8a77-duz3Pa45HycE25js1GN7g=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73427405/247132_TECH_MOVING_WEEK_JGIBBSLEDE_2040x1360.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Jackson Gibbs for The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"USdHkl\">Moving is one of the most stressful events that can happen in your life. It takes a lot of time and effort, it\u2019s expensive, it\u2019s complicated, and there\u2019s just a ton to do. </p>\n<p id=\"0exZKr\">It\u2019s not just a matter of finding a place you can afford, signing the lease or arranging for a mortgage, and figuring out how to get your stuff from one place to another. There are also a variety of other issues. You probably have to downsize and declutter before you move. You have to figure out which furniture to move, and which to keep, and get rid of all those", "id": 827110, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/24185638/moving-tech-how-to-tips-hacks", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "The Verge\u2019s guide to moving", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-07-08T12:15:00+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Illustration of a person holding back a mountain of stuff on the other side of a door.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/UYlZBRefjOX_P-LHZWf97iyTH_I=/2x0:4001x2666/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73448613/247132_GET_RID_OF_STUFF_JGibbs.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Jackson Gibbs for The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n\n  \t\t <p>Moving often means downsizing, and fast. Enter: Facebook Marketplace and Buy Nothing.</p>\n  <p>\n    <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/24163473/moving-sale-facebook-marketplace-buy-nothing-declutter\">Continue reading&hellip;</a>\n  </p>", "id": 827111, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/24163473/moving-sale-facebook-marketplace-buy-nothing-declutter", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "The best way to get rid of all the clutter you don\u2019t need", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-07-08T12:00:00+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Illustration of a person sitting on a couch in the outline of a phone overlayed on top of a scene of the couch being carried in a storm by two movers.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/_0eJ5FKwpnP_F9MWN6CvDO5n-kI=/0x0:4416x2944/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73448566/247132_APPS_TO_HELP_MOVE_JGibbs.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Jackson Gibbs for The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n\n  \t\t <p>From note-taking apps to all-in-one browser tab managers, here are some of the tools that kept me, a massive mess, organized.</p>\n  <p>\n    <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/24164320/notion-onetab-moving-tech-tools-organization\">Continue reading&hellip;</a>\n  </p>", "id": 827112, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/24164320/notion-onetab-moving-tech-tools-organization", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "These apps helped me tame the chaos of a sudden move", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-07-08T11:57:17+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Notepad\u2019s new spellcheck feature\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/p22ynDQ-k8hXhu3jKU0X1C3T4ow=/30x0:1937x1271/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73448544/notepadspellcheck2.0.jpeg\" />\n        <figcaption>Screenshot by Tom Warren / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"SKa3fl\">Microsoft is finally rolling out spellcheck and autocorrect for its Notepad app in Windows 11, more than 40 years after the simple text editor was first introduced in Windows in 1983. The software giant started testing <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/3/21/24107882/notepad-spellcheck-windows-11-feature\">both features in March</a>, and has now quietly started enabling them for all Windows 11 users in recent days.</p>\n<p id=\"3IssmD\">The spellcheck feature in Notepad is almost identical to how Word or Edge highlight misspelled words, with a red underline to clearly show mistakes. I say almost identical because when you right-click on a misspelled word in ", "id": 827113, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/7/8/24194047/microsoft-notepad-spellcheck-autocorrect-features-available", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Microsoft\u2019s Notepad gets spellcheck and autocorrect 40 years after launch", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-07-08T11:46:25+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Paramount Pictures studio lot at 5555 Melrose Ave.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/h9Ezvoo1iiN9lZc9G5E-UAvbY0w=/767x69:2834x1447/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73448540/2155619483.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>Skydance founder David Ellison is set to become Paramount\u2019s new chairman and chief executive.</em> | Brian van der Brug / Los Angeles Times via Getty Images</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"AiPB8k\">Paramount Global has agreed to merge with Skydance Media in a deal that will see the joint enterprise, temporarily dubbed \u201cNew Paramount,\u201d valued at approximately $28 billion.</p>\n<p id=\"ly8mAW\">As part of the <a href=\"https://ir.paramount.com/news-releases/news-release-details/skydance-media-and-paramount-global-sign-definitive-agreement\">two-step agreement announced on Sunday</a>, Paramount Chair Shari Redstone (the daughter of Sumner Redstone) will sell National Amusements \u2014 which holds her family\u2019s controlling stake in Pa", "id": 827114, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/7/8/24194043/paramount-skydance-merger-deal-announced-28-billion", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Paramount agrees to sweetened Skydance merger deal", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-07-08T09:13:08+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/1dv7meyKcn-AlRBtTf_0v2E3e-k=/0x0:2640x1760/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73448434/rgbwindows.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>You can now control the ROG lighting in Windows.</em> | Photo by Tom Warren / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"X3h9Y8\">Asus is planning to support Microsoft\u2019s new Dynamic Lighting feature that allows Windows 11 users to control a motherboard\u2019s RGB lighting without needing a separate app. Asus has started testing new beta BIOS updates for both of its <a href=\"https://rog-forum.asus.com/t5/amd-600-series/x670-resource/m-p/1026026/highlight/true#M6656\">AMD 600</a> and <a href=\"https://rog-forum.asus.com/t5/intel-700-600-series/raptorlake-resources/m-p/1024858/highlight/true#M23638\">Intel 700</a> series motherboards that include the Dynamic Lighting support.</p>\n<p id=\"nmwnBv\">Microsoft <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2023/5/23/23734501/windows-11-rgb-dynamic-ligh", "id": 826133, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/7/8/24194015/asus-windows-dynamic-lighting-support-motherboard-bios-update", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Asus is adding RGB Windows Dynamic Lighting support to its latest motherboards", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-07-08T09:02:04+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Planes Fly At Sydney Airport As Boeing 737 MAX 8 Operations Are Suspended In Australia\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0X1I2Hoz0eppN1na4byH5U0FHCQ=/0x0:3000x2000/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73448430/1135669563.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>Boeing\u2019s plea deal must receive the approval of a federal judge to take effect.</em> | Photo by Cameron Spencer/Getty Images</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"KdkBCZ\">Boeing has agreed to plead guilty to a criminal fraud charge related to a pair of crashes of its 737 Max planes, as part of a plea deal with the US Department of Justice. Lawyers for the victims\u2019 families plan to object to the deal, which was forged on Sunday just before a midnight deadline and must still be approved by a federal judge.</p>\n<p id=\"jPGmIY\">The two crashes, which happened in 2018 and 2019, killed more than 300 people. The planes malfunctioned because of software that was intended to correct for a design flaw \u2014", "id": 826134, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/7/8/24190142/boeing-737-max-doj-guilty-plea-deal-accepted", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Boeing accepts guilty plea deal over 737 Max crashes", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-07-08T09:00:00+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Nothing CMF Phone 1\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/nu64a1HcvKnyl6EEqAa2Tp2E9Vo=/0x45:2000x1378/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73448414/DSC07577.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>Honestly, this is Nothing\u2019s best idea yet.</em></figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"xfCzPx\">I\u2019ve never had so much fun taking a phone apart.</p>\n<p id=\"m5QQzM\">That\u2019s a misleading statement; I haven\u2019t really taken <em>any </em>phones apart lately, but when CMF\u2019s Phone 1 arrived, that\u2019s the first thing I did. Because this one, my friends, is built different. It won\u2019t be widely available in the US, but if you\u2019re game, you can get one through Nothing\u2019s beta program \u2014 and for $199, that\u2019s seriously tempting.</p>\n<p id=\"v3axBG\">CMF, Nothing\u2019s <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2023/8/3/23818715/nothing-cmf-subbrand-affordable-carl-pei\">budget-conscious but still extremely style-driven subbrand</a>, is shipping its first phone, the aptly named Phone 1. While it sh", "id": 826135, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/7/8/24191666/nothing-cmf-phone-1-cases-accessories-lanyard-wallet", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Nothing\u2019s CMF Phone 1 is proof that gadgets can still be fun", "user": null, "vote": 0}]